theorem
fixes n :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 5"
and h1 : "\<forall> k. k \<le> n \<longrightarrow> odd k"
shows  "(\<Sum>k\<in>{1..n}. k) = 25"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 What is the sum of the first five positive odd integers? The final Answer is 25
 ### Proof

 *)
